title: "Fear the Walking Dead" Has the Highest-Rated First Season in Cable History
text:
"Fear the Walking Dead" Has the Highest-Rated First Season in Cable History Posted just a moment ago 
Frank Ockenfels 3/AMC (LOS ANGELES) -- The Walking Dead effect continues to have an impact on AMC in the ratings. The first season of their spin-off, Fear the Walking Dead , has become cable's highest-rated series ever. 
According to Variety , the series' six episodes averaged 11.2 million viewers, with 7.3 million adults in the coveted 18-49 demographic. In fact, last Sunday's season finale clocked in 10.11 million viewers overall -- a number that includes live viewers along with Video On Demand and DVR recordings watched three days after the initial airing. 
Fans who can't get enough of The Walking Dead can get their fill Sunday when the sixth season kicks off at 9 p.m. Eastern.
